{
  "texts": [
    "Most service members lived on post (67.2%).",
    "Participants had been in the military for an average of 3.2 years (SD=3.0).",
    "Average time in the current unit was 9.1 months (SD = 4.6).",
    "The most common military occupational specialty (MOS) was infantry (58.7%), followed by field artillery (12.4%), and armor/tanks (11.6%), medical (6.1%) and maintenance (4.5%).",
    "Online surveys were collected approximately one month prior to intervention activities and again approximately three months after baseline."
  ]
}